[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Kotlin's callable references**\n\nI’m reflecting on the Kotlin specification regarding callable references, especially about inline functions. My understanding is that while a callable reference to an inline function is acceptable, it appears to lose its inline property. I wonder about callable references specifically to reified type parameters — does that follow the same logic? It’s intriguing to think about how these nuances affect performance and type safety in Kotlin programming. I need to dig deeper into that to clarify!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f0689f477e11fa4016a3c8cd0cefc8195b82a9555b4991644\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPIzkFK_cW_F5KcaOX3lNFcyQttuDGtVG_8SrYPj3YZNSek5sWSxeoPNeNP_HXfnlEP5viR9yT1RhFX1VDnMiaQpsfFh19E5Lyq86D7Oqcx7rYMnGDWw9GdBDXXkuXIaw-zX81h4UHq5avQ2m3OBeHTYErelblLfejdn-1gPBq0YqEdTXOXI7dF6j4cs9aj8wNi-vIK1IpHMUajOg09rggO_J_Qk4-r_uGzzUIzSl4qLehNg9A2ZXvS3y4jG3JDD-Z1TKCuw0xZHMd2BTs4PZoronb0ZQx3dy8BKabgLwdQR2E7y_10AANQQoLqHJfqG9-MK-wEG0RJojmh_a6yI3fZre-U6__5MShpI7plH5KKHzeD0qYgb58KEYeKabj5G3aXkKAMIwP4x-VujeAHa7FjVprLKRTyiMezuIsaWcLHxKhs21XHOG-DwIAhuFDsz2Oex15huJqoHifXsdiP0b8ICdmRLAf4_pDIZLbJ_dohJsDZNevH3qzXhv2GXmHuSsEVTor5_zq7WnmygArdKMfG_vK8HhSgf3ItbHmX_b8frs-16eTgMgxMB7Kte-PruNM_ilTorlf96KKNP2_JWPcoBa0aJ8yAVOgXOcZca8h-2Pi0FKe2iv1ZoKAj8_CaAjyjvy-ac61tyqAg8FrDgTe711RyXNaNheZI8mjDab51FqKg9nNdmA4Y0hQOa6BB8KQ_lyKMIgH22NZ2d1j5L93yrzzRbx9_EIbbM0QZ2fTRH3WXPZhODIkeET9vT4acZJlqrqiG3tbYX60LhGDk1Ckm-8ZOUWGKZzb03RPj8uG0l6XExXXRNUp1WlWvfAeBXtuDr_Q8wVbxrhqtMPXJQgRfscb6aYpOTNY4nftv4vjRVkhc9_fCcNMyidyVnhzPfPU0fiYfAAg6cTsRPQ3PFxCvWX-uJqw1W3ciV6cm89hJ8zfAblCqoKbbhaOvG5Jvk2ZAWTsAbciAFs0xYHkQ_4W0Weqhsc9q4Im9lzXVDzjl6huaMtbOD1ipangsPj8c7sypdMbTTCkhjdc8FCgD6DQ_SK787LlEJ5Idr5YF_tAx0qrqFyrHojhjApdGHF4JE5fgS7aPH_zDa6_cd-S-DwiX07rCsiIsOLrcAcpMILRNYalBUHyXDbZQxzD16xqfOXlZmlSCPa3w7gCApDFtO2Zk3pRs4Uu3bp